726978f-b.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - Parsons Boulevard
726978f-b.text:
Jamaica Avenue, at the N.E. corner of Parsons
Boulevard, showing the former damaica Town Hall,
erected in 1869. 1909 and 1918 atlases refer to it
as the Municipal Building and the 1929 atlas as the
Court House.
View 1: About 1900
View 2: 1922

726979f-a.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - Parsons Boulevard
726979f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave. (elevated structure thereon), at the N.W. corner of
Parsons Boulevard, showing at the corner the Wm. Phraner house of
1873. The Higbie Building now (1934) stands on this site. Dr. Peter
L. Hull (dentist) was the oaner of the entire block frontage for many
years. In 1923 Robert W. Higbie leased the entire block front.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
